title: The Surprising Adventures of Baron Munchausen
creator: Rudolf Erich Raspe
description: LibriVox recording of The Surprising Adventures of Baron Munchausen, by Rudolf Erich Raspe. Read by volunteer readers. The stories about Münchhausen were first collected and published by an anonymous author in 1781. An English version was published in London in 1785, by Rudolf Erich Raspe, as Baron Munchhausen's Narrative of his Marvellous Travels and Campaigns in Russia, also called The Surprising Adventures of Baron Munchhausen. It is not clear how much of the story material derives from the Baron himself; however, it is known that the majority of the stories are based on folktales that have been in circulation for many centuries before Münchhausen's birth. (Summary by Wikipedia) M4B audiobook of complete book For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: Librivox; audiobook; folk tales; fantasy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Humorous stories read by performers who are obviously having a wonderful time.  Simply a great recording: one of theb est I've listened to on Librivox.
